TYPHOID FEVER UPDATE 2012 (02): ZIMBABWE (HARARE)
*************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Wed 25 Jan 2012
Source: Daily Monitor (Uganda) [edited]
http://www.monitor.co.ug/News/World/-/688340/1313282/-/120t766/-/


A fresh typhoid outbreak in the Zimbabwean capital Harare has left 600 residents infected and 90 hospitalized in the past few days.

Authorities warned that the outbreak that had been initially confined to populated suburbs was fast spreading to the entire city after a hotel employee was hospitalized. "We have confirmed that the disease is typhoid. It has been caused by contaminated foodstuffs sold in the open," said Dr Prosper Chonzi, the city's director of health services.

"One of the confirmed cases is a person who works in a city hotel. If people eat food handled by the person, they risk contracting typhoid."

The outbreak in Harare has been worsened by collapsing sewer infrastructure with authorities saying water samples taken from the worst affected area showed that it contained human waste.

"We have attended to over 600 cases in one suburb alone. We have not recorded any deaths," he said. He said most of the victims ate fish from a lake on the outskirts of Harare, which environmentalists say has been heavily polluted by sewage flowing from the capital.

[Byline: Kitsepile Nyathi]

